ve processing.";i:24;s:46:"This game is like musical chairs but creative.";i:25;s:41:"It can be adapted for all fitness levels.";i:26;s:113:"Tell each participant to start drawing and when the music stops they give the picture to the person next to them.";i:27;s:86:"Continue to play music change and draw until everyone has their original drawing back.";i:28;s:62:"Admire the strange masterpieces you have all created together.";i:29;s:125:"Seniors may not realize how much a a workout they can get from chair exercises but the classes can be fun and very effective.";i:30;s:32:"The music and movement lift the.";i:31;s:258:"For 2 years now I have been a member of a musical group mostly senior uke players and we play and sing in nursing homes hospitals or whenever the group is invited to provide musical entertainment in events such as awareness of Mental Health Week or Dementia.";i:32;s:80:"I find this activity not only therapeutic for our audience but to me personally.";i:33;s:48:"Sit upright and away from the back of the chair.";i:34;s:34:"Pull your shoulders back and down.";i:35;s:33:"Extend your arms out to the side.";i:36;s:81:"Gently push your chest forward and up until you feel a stretch across your chest.";i:37;s:44:"Hold for 5 to 10 seconds and repeat 5 times.";i:38;s:86:"Upper-body twist This stretch will develop and maintain flexibility in the upper back.";i:39;s:110:"Lauretta Jennings of Hingham developed a fun chair exercise program for seniors four years ago called Chaboom.";i:40;s:55:"And it is still going strong at area senior residences.";i:41;s:88:"This video from 2012 shows how dynamic sitting in one place can be with the right music.";i:42;s:37:"Easy Warm Up Exercises for Seniors 1.";i:43;s:49:"Leg Swings Warm Up Chair Exercises for Seniors 5.";i:44;s:23:"Seated Ankle Circles 6.";i:45;s:27:"Seated Hamstring Stretch 7.";i:46;s:22:"Seated Shin Stretch 8.";i:47;s:57:"Seated Hip Lifts Tai Chi Warm Up Exercises for Seniors 9.";i:48;s:243:"Ageless Grace incorporates systemic movements through the use of 21 playful exercise tools designed for lifelong comfort and ease set to upbeat music targeting all parts of the body and all five functions of the brain while sitting in a chair.";i:49;s:85:"Ageless Grace Chair Exercises for Seniors Being in a chair has some great advantages.";i:50;s:121:"Chair exercises for seniors are a multi-dimensional set of exercises aim to provide a well-rounded workout for your body.";i:51;s:174:"Practicing these exercise will not only help to build your muscles stronger but will also increase your metabolism and blood circulation giving you a sense of accomplishment.";i:52;s:110:"To start chair exercise seniors you can try to discuss it with seniors about the activities that will be done.";i:53;s:69:"Give a simple understanding of what will be done with chair exercise.";i:54;s:112:"After getting a positive response from seniors you can prepare the equipment in the form of a comfortable chair.";}}